    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-07T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-07T15:00:00-05:00" n="782"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d782">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2100</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-07T21:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1915, 9 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 8, 11 a. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2854. I have had no news from you about submarine negotiations, notes, or
                    position. <persName corresp="#p_JGEGV1">Von Jagow</persName> complained to-day
                    that he had no news whatever from <persName corresp="#p_BJHACV1"
                        >Bernstorff</persName>; that as you have German cipher, communication of
                    confidential nature by wireless is useless and that you refuse to transmit
                    cipher to <persName corresp="#p_BJHACV1">Bernstorff</persName> through me. Hope
                    you will at least let me know what has happened and authorize me to inform
                        <persName corresp="#p_JGEGV1">Von Jagow</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
